63/*
64 * For now we only support 8 and 16 octet tags. The spec allows for
65 * optional 12 byte tag, which may be supported in the future.
66 */
67#define GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN 16
68#define GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN_8 8
69
70/*
71 * This function allocates a new instance of this crypto engine.
72 * The key_len parameter should be one of 28 or 44 for
73 * AES-128-GCM or AES-256-GCM respectively. Note that the
74 * key length includes the 14 byte salt value that is used when
75 * initializing the KDF.
76 */
77static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_alloc(srtp_cipher_t **c,
78 int key_len,
79 int tlen)
80{
81 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *gcm;
82
83 debug_print(srtp_mod_aes_gcm, "allocating cipher with key length %d",
84 key_len);
85 debug_print(srtp_mod_aes_gcm, "allocating cipher with tag length %d", tlen);
86
87 /*
88 * Verify the key_len is valid for one of: AES-128/256
89 */
90 if (key_len != SRTP_AES_GCM_128_KEY_LEN_WSALT &&
91 key_len != SRTP_AES_GCM_256_KEY_LEN_WSALT) {
92 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
93 }
94
95 if (tlen != GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN && tlen != GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN_8) {
96 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
97 }
98
99 /* allocate memory a cipher of type aes_gcm */
100 *c = (srtp_cipher_t *)srtp_crypto_alloc(sizeof(srtp_cipher_t));
101 if (*c == NULL) {
102 return (srtp_err_status_alloc_fail);
103 }
104
105 gcm = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)srtp_crypto_alloc(sizeof(srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t));
106 if (gcm == NULL) {
107 srtp_crypto_free(*c);
108 *c = NULL;
109 return (srtp_err_status_alloc_fail);
110 }
111
112 gcm->ctx = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_new();
113 if (gcm->ctx == NULL) {
114 srtp_crypto_free(gcm);
115 srtp_crypto_free(*c);
116 *c = NULL;
117 return srtp_err_status_alloc_fail;
118 }
119
120 /* set pointers */
121 (*c)->state = gcm;
122
123 /* setup cipher attributes */
124 switch (key_len) {
125 case SRTP_AES_GCM_128_KEY_LEN_WSALT:
126 (*c)->type = &srtp_aes_gcm_128;
127 (*c)->algorithm = SRTP_AES_GCM_128;
128 gcm->key_size = SRTP_AES_128_KEY_LEN;
129 gcm->tag_len = tlen;
130 break;
131 case SRTP_AES_GCM_256_KEY_LEN_WSALT:
132 (*c)->type = &srtp_aes_gcm_256;
133 (*c)->algorithm = SRTP_AES_GCM_256;
134 gcm->key_size = SRTP_AES_256_KEY_LEN;
135 gcm->tag_len = tlen;
136 break;
137 }
138
139 /* set key size */
140 (*c)->key_len = key_len;
141
142 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
143}
144
145/*
146 * This function deallocates a GCM session
147 */
148static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_dealloc(srtp_cipher_t *c)
149{
150 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *ctx;
151
152 ctx = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)c->state;
153 if (ctx) {
154 EVP_CIPHER_CTX_free(ctx->ctx);
155 /* zeroize the key material */
156 octet_string_set_to_zero(ctx, sizeof(srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t));
157 srtp_crypto_free(ctx);
158 }
159
160 /* free memory */
161 srtp_crypto_free(c);
162
163 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
164}
165
166/*
167 * aes_gcm_openssl_context_init(...) initializes the aes_gcm_context
168 * using the value in key[].
169 *
170 * the key is the secret key
171 */
172static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_context_init(void *cv,
173 const uint8_t *key)
174{
175 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
176 const EVP_CIPHER *evp;
177
178 c->dir = srtp_direction_any;
179
180 debug_print(srtp_mod_aes_gcm, "key: %s",
181 srtp_octet_string_hex_string(key, c->key_size));
182
183 switch (c->key_size) {
184 case SRTP_AES_256_KEY_LEN:
185 evp = EVP_aes_256_gcm();
186 break;
187 case SRTP_AES_128_KEY_LEN:
188 evp = EVP_aes_128_gcm();
189 break;
190 default:
191 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
192 break;
193 }
194
195 EVP_CIPHER_CTX_cleanup(c->ctx);
196 if (!EVP_CipherInit_ex(c->ctx, evp, NULL, key, NULL, 0)) {
197 return (srtp_err_status_init_fail);
198 }
199
200 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
201}
202
203/*
204 * aes_gcm_openssl_set_iv(c, iv) sets the counter value to the exor of iv with
205 * the offset
206 */
207static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_set_iv(
208 void *cv,
209 uint8_t *iv,
210 srtp_cipher_direction_t direction)
211{
212 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
213
214 if (direction != srtp_direction_encrypt &&
215 direction != srtp_direction_decrypt) {
216 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
217 }
218 c->dir = direction;
219
220 debug_print(srtp_mod_aes_gcm, "setting iv: %s",
221 srtp_octet_string_hex_string(iv, 12));
222
223 if (!EVP_CIPHER_CTX_ctrl(c->ctx, EVP_CTRL_GCM_SET_IVLEN, 12, 0)) {
224 return (srtp_err_status_init_fail);
225 }
226
227 if (!EVP_CipherInit_ex(c->ctx, NULL, NULL, NULL, iv,
228 (c->dir == srtp_direction_encrypt ? 1 : 0))) {
229 return (srtp_err_status_init_fail);
230 }
231
232 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
233}
234
235/*
236 * This function processes the AAD
237 *
238 * Parameters:
239 * c Crypto context
240 * aad Additional data to process for AEAD cipher suites
241 * aad_len length of aad buffer
242 */
243static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_set_aad(void *cv,
244 const uint8_t *aad,
245 uint32_t aad_len)
246{
247 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
248 int rv;
249
250 debug_print(srtp_mod_aes_gcm, "setting AAD: %s",
251 srtp_octet_string_hex_string(aad, aad_len));
252
253 /*
254 * EVP_CTRL_GCM_SET_TAG can only be used when decrypting
255 */
256 if (c->dir == srtp_direction_decrypt) {
257 /*
258 * Set dummy tag, OpenSSL requires the Tag to be set before
259 * processing AAD
260 */
261
262 /*
263 * OpenSSL never write to address pointed by the last parameter of
264 * EVP_CIPHER_CTX_ctrl while EVP_CTRL_GCM_SET_TAG (in reality,
265 * OpenSSL copy its content to the context), so we can make
266 * aad read-only in this function and all its wrappers.
267 */
268 unsigned char dummy_tag[GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN];
269 memset(dummy_tag, 0x0, GCM_AUTH_TAG_LEN);
270 if (!EVP_CIPHER_CTX_ctrl(c->ctx, EVP_CTRL_GCM_SET_TAG, c->tag_len,
271 &dummy_tag)) {
272 return (srtp_err_status_algo_fail);
273 }
274 }
275
276 rv = EVP_Cipher(c->ctx, NULL, aad, aad_len);
277 if (rv != aad_len) {
278 return (srtp_err_status_algo_fail);
279 } else {
280 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
281 }
282}
283
284/*
285 * This function encrypts a buffer using AES GCM mode
286 *
287 * Parameters:
288 * c Crypto context
289 * buf data to encrypt
290 * enc_len length of encrypt buffer
291 */
292static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_encrypt(void *cv,
293 unsigned char *buf,
294 unsigned int *enc_len)
295{
296 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
297 if (c->dir != srtp_direction_encrypt && c->dir != srtp_direction_decrypt) {
298 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
299 }
300
301 /*
302 * Encrypt the data
303 */
304 EVP_Cipher(c->ctx, buf, buf, *enc_len);
305
306 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
307}
308
309/*
310 * This function calculates and returns the GCM tag for a given context.
311 * This should be called after encrypting the data. The *len value
312 * is increased by the tag size. The caller must ensure that *buf has
313 * enough room to accept the appended tag.
314 *
315 * Parameters:
316 * c Crypto context
317 * buf data to encrypt
318 * len length of encrypt buffer
319 */
320static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_get_tag(void *cv,
321 uint8_t *buf,
322 uint32_t *len)
323{
324 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
325 /*
326 * Calculate the tag
327 */
328 EVP_Cipher(c->ctx, NULL, NULL, 0);
329
330 /*
331 * Retreive the tag
332 */
333 if (!EVP_CIPHER_CTX_ctrl(c->ctx, EVP_CTRL_GCM_GET_TAG, c->tag_len, buf)) {
334 return (srtp_err_status_algo_fail);
335 }
336
337 /*
338 * Increase encryption length by desired tag size
339 */
340 *len = c->tag_len;
341
342 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
343}
344
345/*
346 * This function decrypts a buffer using AES GCM mode
347 *
348 * Parameters:
349 * c Crypto context
350 * buf data to encrypt
351 * enc_len length of encrypt buffer
352 */
353static srtp_err_status_t srtp_aes_gcm_openssl_decrypt(void *cv,
354 unsigned char *buf,
355 unsigned int *enc_len)
356{
357 srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *c = (srtp_aes_gcm_ctx_t *)cv;
358 if (c->dir != srtp_direction_encrypt && c->dir != srtp_direction_decrypt) {
359 return (srtp_err_status_bad_param);
360 }
361
362 /*
363 * Set the tag before decrypting
364 */
365 if (!EVP_CIPHER_CTX_ctrl(c->ctx, EVP_CTRL_GCM_SET_TAG, c->tag_len,
366 buf + (*enc_len - c->tag_len))) {
367 return (srtp_err_status_auth_fail);
368 }
369 EVP_Cipher(c->ctx, buf, buf, *enc_len - c->tag_len);
370
371 /*
372 * Check the tag
373 */
374 if (EVP_Cipher(c->ctx, NULL, NULL, 0)) {
375 return (srtp_err_status_auth_fail);
376 }
377
378 /*
379 * Reduce the buffer size by the tag length since the tag
380 * is not part of the original payload
381 */
382 *enc_len -= c->tag_len;
383
384 return (srtp_err_status_ok);
385}
